
---


@startuml

' Entities
class Customer {
    - id: int
    - name: string
    - vatNumber: string
    - headOfficeAddress: Address
}

class Address {
    - id: int
    - street: string
    - city: string
    - zipCode: string
    - country: string
}

class Product {
    - id: int
    - name: string
    - description: string
    - unitPrice: decimal
    - stockQuantity: int
}

class Order {
    - id: int
    - customer: Customer
    - orderDate: datetime
    - paymentDate: datetime (optional)
    - isFullyPaid: boolean
    - isFullyShipped: boolean
}

class OrderLine {
    - id: int
    - product: Product
    - quantityOrdered: int
    - quantityShipped: int
    - order: Order
    - status: enum { Pending, PartiallyShipped, FullyShipped }
}

class Shipment {
    - id: int
    - shipmentDate: datetime
    - deliveryStatus: enum { Packed, Shipped, Delivered, Lost, Damaged }
    - deliveryServiceUsed: string
}

class Delivery {
    - id: int
    - shipment: Shipment
    - address: Address
    - orderLines: list<OrderLine>
    - deliveryDate: datetime (optional)
    - receivedBy: string
}

class Invoice {
    - id: int
    - order: Order
    - invoiceDate: datetime
    - totalAmount: decimal
    - paymentDueDate: datetime
    - isPaid: boolean
}

' Associations and Multiplicities
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Order : places
Order "1" -- "1" Invoice : generates
Order "1" -- "1..*" OrderLine : contains
OrderLine "1" -- "1" Product : forProduct
Customer "1" -- "1" Address : hasHeadOffice
Customer "0..*" -- "0..*" Address : hasDeliveryAddress
Address "0..*" -- "0..*" OrderLine : usedForDelivery
OrderLine "1" -- "0..*" Delivery : shippedIn
Delivery "1" -- "1" Shipment : partOf
Shipment "1" -- "1" Delivery : includes
Invoice "1" -- "1" Order : relatesTo

' Constraints
note right of OrderLine
    quantityShipped <= quantityOrdered
end note

note right of Order
    isFullyShipped = true iff all OrderLines are FullyShipped
    isFullyPaid = true iff paymentDate is set
end note

note right of Shipment
    A shipment may include multiple deliveries.
    Each delivery can have one or more order lines.
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Key Features Covered:

- **Customers**: Can have both a head office and delivery addresses.
- **Orders & OrderLines**: Support partial shipments per line.
- **Stock Management**: Products track current stock levels.
- **Payment Options**: Orders can be paid at time of placing or after delivery.
- **Invoicing**: Invoices are generated and linked to orders.
- **Shipping Enhancements**:
  - **Shipments** represent groups of delivered items.
  - **Deliveries** handle actual shipping events with statuses.
  - **Partial shipments** are supported by tracking `quantityShipped` in each `OrderLine`.
- **Tracking & Accountability**:
  - Shipment status (`Packed`, `Shipped`, `Delivered`, etc.)
  - Ability to log delivery issues (`Lost`, `Damaged`)

